00:38:21.390 --> 00:38:25.630
who goes to court
complaining that her--

00:38:25.630 --> 00:38:26.930
the inhabitants

00:38:26.930 --> 00:38:30.400
of her neighborhood are
preventing her from remarrying.

00:38:30.400 --> 00:38:33.380
And her husband allegedly
passed away four years ago.

00:38:33.380 --> 00:38:36.580
She's been told by
someone that he had died.

00:38:36.580 --> 00:38:40.360
And she wants to remarry which
is a very common scenario.

00:38:40.360 --> 00:38:44.470
It was pretty much on her
to-- for people to not marry,

00:38:44.470 --> 00:38:45.770
you know, Ottoman society.

00:38:45.770 --> 00:38:48.620
So everybody married and
remarried for the most part.

00:38:48.620 --> 00:38:51.310
Very few people married
only once from the records

00:38:51.310 --> 00:38:54.780
as far as we can tell.

00:38:54.780 --> 00:38:59.760
So he-- she's asking for
the right to be divorced

00:38:59.760 --> 00:39:04.050
so she can remarry in the
absence of her husband.

00:39:04.050 --> 00:39:05.960
And the court grants her wish.

00:39:05.960 --> 00:39:08.390
So she's divorced
from her husband

00:39:08.390 --> 00:39:09.690
and she's free to remarry.

00:39:09.690 --> 00:39:11.660
And the neighborhood
residents are told

00:39:11.660 --> 00:39:13.300
to leave her alone, basically.

00:39:13.300 --> 00:39:16.700
Now here is another case.

00:39:16.700 --> 00:39:21.440
Let's take a moment
to read and see

00:39:21.440 --> 00:39:24.320
if anybody can tell
me what is different

00:39:24.320 --> 00:39:25.620
between these two cases.

00:39:25.620 --> 00:39:29.450
They're very similar
but also different.

00:39:29.450 --> 00:39:34.160
Yeah. So we have a
Christian woman here.

00:39:35.360 --> 00:39:37.050
An Armenian.

00:39:37.050 --> 00:39:40.090
So what is she doing
at the qadi court?

00:39:40.090 --> 00:39:42.430
Why is she at the Sharia court?

00:39:44.060 --> 00:39:45.900
Right? Well, she's
supposed to go

00:39:45.900 --> 00:39:50.270
to her orthodox Christian
courts, they're there.

00:39:50.270 --> 00:39:52.080
And the law is specifying

00:39:52.080 --> 00:39:54.510
that she should go
to her own community.

00:39:54.510 --> 00:40:00.930
But it's actually really
common to see non-Muslim women

00:40:00.930 --> 00:40:04.740
in the Sharia courts, which
is intriguing and amazing.

00:40:04.740 --> 00:40:06.110
This is why we love history

00:40:06.110 --> 00:40:08.250
and this work is
like detective work.

00:40:08.250 --> 00:40:14.070
So why would non-Muslim women
go to the Islamic courts, right.

00:40:14.070 --> 00:40:17.470
So in this case, again, the
court decides in favor of her.

00:40:17.470 --> 00:40:19.870
And this is sort of
based on the Sharia

00:40:19.870 --> 00:40:21.940
and maybe some of the law codes.

00:40:21.940 --> 00:40:24.880
But technically speaking,
there is this nice division

00:40:24.880 --> 00:40:29.440
between different
religious communities, right.

00:40:29.440 --> 00:40:33.580
In fact, going to the
Sharia courts were so common

00:40:33.580 --> 00:40:35.310
that in Istanbul the patriarchs

00:40:35.310 --> 00:40:37.550
in both the Greek
Orthodox Armenian

00:40:37.550 --> 00:40:42.070
and Jewish communities
periodically petitioned the

00:40:42.070 --> 00:40:47.340
Ottoman Palace and religious
dignitaries to stop it

00:40:47.340 --> 00:40:50.230
from happening because
they want to have control

00:40:50.230 --> 00:40:51.850
over their own communities so--

00:40:51.850 --> 00:40:55.590
and they kept going
to the Sharia courts.

00:40:55.590 --> 00:40:59.210
So, I mean some of the
reasons are obvious

00:40:59.210 --> 00:41:02.890
because from what we know, and I
have to say, I haven't ever done

00:41:02.890 --> 00:41:04.260
in the research in the courts--

00:41:04.260 --> 00:41:06.240
court records of
those communities.

00:41:06.240 --> 00:41:08.800
So this is from secondary
literature.

00:41:08.800 --> 00:41:11.750
But Orthodox Christian law,
when a marriage was annulled,

00:41:11.750 --> 00:41:15.310
the husband did not return to
his wife the premarital donation

00:41:15.310 --> 00:41:16.990
or the drahoma, given

00:41:16.990 --> 00:41:22.530
by the prospective bride's
family to the groom.

00:41:22.530 --> 00:41:25.270
And Jewish women had to get
from their husbands a bill

00:41:25.270 --> 00:41:29.180
of divorce, again, that only
the husband could issue.

00:41:29.180 --> 00:41:32.900
But by comparison Muslim
women-- in the Islamic courts,

00:41:32.900 --> 00:41:34.200
women had some options.

00:41:34.200 --> 00:41:37.990
So there were more options
in the Islamic courts.

00:41:37.990 --> 00:41:41.720
And so because of this, we
see that non-Muslim women went

00:41:41.720 --> 00:41:43.640
to the courts to
register their marriages

00:41:43.640 --> 00:41:46.070
so that they could go back
when something happened and ask

00:41:46.070 --> 00:41:49.680
for a divorce in
the court as well.

00:41:49.680 --> 00:41:52.950
So I really don't know about
the applicability of this

00:41:52.950 --> 00:41:56.920
in other Islamic Sharia courts,
but I know it happened regularly

00:41:56.920 --> 00:41:58.490
in the Ottoman Empire in places

00:41:58.490 --> 00:42:00.700
like Damascus, in
Aleppo and Cairo.

00:42:00.700 --> 00:42:04.810
This is not just in Istanbul.

00:42:04.810 --> 00:42:16.940
But again, at this point, I
want to say that my goal is not

00:42:16.940 --> 00:42:20.460
to make a statement about which
type of law was more impressive

00:42:20.460 --> 00:42:22.280
or more patriarchal,
whether Jewish

00:42:22.280 --> 00:42:25.990
or the Christian Law was more
repressive than Islamic Law.

00:42:25.990 --> 00:42:27.340
But rather, my point is

00:42:27.340 --> 00:42:29.620
that these women
shared a common culture,

00:42:29.620 --> 00:42:32.690
a common patriarchal culture
which did not easily allow them

00:42:32.690 --> 00:42:36.220
to divorce or remarry, right,
whatever religion they were.

00:42:36.220 --> 00:42:41.320
But the Islamic courts gave
them some extra options.

00:42:41.320 --> 00:42:45.270
All right, another
example of grounds

00:42:45.270 --> 00:42:48.620
for divorce is impotence.

00:42:48.620 --> 00:42:50.470
So the sexual incompetence

00:42:50.470 --> 00:42:53.030
of the husband is
a legitimate ground

00:42:53.030 --> 00:42:56.730
for a divorce in Sharia law.

00:42:56.730 --> 00:42:59.830
Again, there is the issue of
in the absence of medical--

00:42:59.830 --> 00:43:03.460
modern medicine, like how do
you prove that, what do you do,

00:43:03.460 --> 00:43:05.380
or how long do you wait?

00:43:05.380 --> 00:43:09.000
There are very clear
instructions

00:43:09.000 --> 00:43:14.200
in Sharia principles that
talk about a woman finding

00:43:14.200 --> 00:43:16.650
out on the first day or
night of their marriage

00:43:16.650 --> 00:43:22.170
that the husband some kind
of hideous deforming disease

00:43:22.170 --> 00:43:25.290
or is incapable of
having an erection,

00:43:25.290 --> 00:43:29.400
or that something terribly
goes wrong on that first day.

00:43:29.400 --> 00:43:31.120
So the woman has the right to go

00:43:31.120 --> 00:43:32.970
to court immediately
to report that.

00:43:32.970 --> 00:43:35.730
And there are records
of it in the courts.

00:43:35.730 --> 00:43:40.180
But more broadly, we also
have evidence of, you know,

00:43:40.180 --> 00:43:44.720
women going to court and
oftentimes the judge grants

00:43:44.720 --> 00:43:46.020
like a waiting period.

00:43:46.020 --> 00:43:48.930
Like he gives like a year or
something and says like work

00:43:48.930 --> 00:43:52.260
on it, it's probably, I'm not
sure but there is a period.

00:43:52.260 --> 00:43:55.920
And then within that period, if
the marriage is not consummated,

00:43:55.920 --> 00:43:57.770
then the woman gets the divorce

00:43:57.770 --> 00:44:02.420
because there was a
basic understanding

00:44:02.420 --> 00:44:06.330
of the basic rights, basic
conditions or exigencies

00:44:06.330 --> 00:44:09.880
of civic life, right, that
everybody was entitled to.

00:44:09.880 --> 00:44:12.610
And these categories refer
to the servants of God

00:44:12.610 --> 00:44:17.150
in Ottoman Sharia law and it
included non-Muslims, right.

00:44:17.150 --> 00:44:21.410
So everybody is entitled
to life property progeny.

00:44:21.410 --> 00:44:23.380
So, if you're not
consummating your marriage

00:44:23.380 --> 00:44:26.210
and that's a violation
of your basic rights

00:44:26.210 --> 00:44:30.580
and the judge grants
you a divorce.

